sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant FE as browser
    participant GW as api-gateway
    participant AUTH as orches-auth-service
    participant SVC as user-service
    participant DB as user-db
    participant R as Redis

    Note over FE,R: Entry: user clicked reset-password link from lock email (LOG-08 flow)<br/>Account state: hard_locked = true OR login:softlock in Redis (or both)

    rect rgb(240,248,255)
    Note over FE,R: 1. Complete Password Reset

    FE->>GW: POST /auth/reset-password { token, new_password }
    GW->>AUTH: complete_password_reset({ token, new_password })
    AUTH->>AUTH: validate token → resolve user_id
    end

    rect rgb(255,248,235)
    Note over FE,R: 2. Update Password + Clear All Lock State

    AUTH->>SVC: reset_password_and_clear_locks(user_id, new_password_hash)
    SVC->>DB: UPDATE users<br/>SET password_hash        = ?,<br/>    failed_login_attempts = 0,<br/>    hard_locked           = false,<br/>    last_failed_login_at  = NULL,<br/>    password_changed_at   = NOW()<br/>WHERE id = ?
    Note right of DB: Single atomic UPDATE<br/>Clears: hard_locked + failed_login_attempts
    DB-->>SVC: updated

    SVC->>R: DEL login:softlock:{userId}
    Note right of R: Unlocks immediately — no need to wait for TTL expiry
    R-->>SVC: OK

    SVC-->>AUTH: { password_reset: true, locks_cleared: true }
    end

    rect rgb(240,255,245)
    Note over FE,R: 3. Confirm to User

    AUTH-->>GW: 200 { message: "Password reset successful." }
    GW-->>FE: 200 { message: "Password reset successful." }
    Note over FE: User may now log in immediately with new password
    end
